  "rationale": "<p>The correct answer is 1/32. Rewrite the roots using fractional exponents: (50n)^(1/4) \u00b7 ((50n)^(1/6))\u00b3 = (50n)^(1/4) \u00b7 (50n)^(3/6) = (50n)^(1/4 + 1/2) = (50n)^(3/4). Setting (50n)^(3/4) = (50n)^(24x) gives 24x = 3/4, so x = 3/96 = 1/32 \u2248 0.0313.</p>",
